.TH ECHOMIND 1 "2025-11-05" "0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
echomind \- Powerful cross-platform AI-powered CLI tool with extensive features
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B echomind
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ PROMPT ]
.br
.B echomind
.B \-\-interactive
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.br
.B echomind
.B \-\-init\-config
.br
.B echomind
.B \-\-clipboard
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B echomind
is a powerful, cross-platform command-line tool written in Rust that pipes input to AI chat APIs and outputs responses. It features extensive support for multiple AI providers, streaming responses, interactive mode, multimodal capabilities, voice features, batch processing, and much more.

When invoked without arguments or input, echomind displays usage information. To process input, pipe text to echomind from stdin, use --clipboard to read from clipboard, or provide input directly.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "General Options"
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output for debugging and performance metrics.
.SS "Mode Options"
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interactive
Start interactive REPL mode for multi-turn conversations.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-coder
Enable coder mode. Generates clean, runnable code without explanations or markdown fences.
.TP
.BR \-\-stream
Stream response as it arrives in real-time (like ChatGPT typing effect).
.TP
.BR \-\-benchmark
Benchmark model performance with timing and metrics.
.TP
.BR \-\-benchmark\-compare " " \fIMODELS\fR
Compare performance across multiple models.
.SS "Input/Output Options"
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Save response to FILE instead of printing to stdout.
.TP
.BR \-\-co " " \fIFILE\fR
Combined shorthand for --coder --output FILE.
.TP
.BR \-\-clipboard
Read input from system clipboard instead of stdin.
.TP
.BR \-\-to\-clipboard
Save response to system clipboard.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: text, json, or template:<template>.
.SS "API Provider Options"
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-provider " " \fINAME\fR
API provider to use. Options: chat, chatanywhere, openai, claude, gemini, ollama, grok, mistral, cohere, or custom URL.
Default: chat (https://ch.at).
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-model " " \fIMODEL\fR
Model to use (e.g., gpt-4, claude-3-opus, gemini-pro, llama2). Default: gpt-3.5-turbo.
.TP
.BR \-\-api\-key " " \fIKEY\fR
API key for providers that require authentication. Can also be set via ECHOMIND_API_KEY environment variable.
.TP
.BR \-\-timeout " " \fISECONDS\fR
Request timeout in seconds. Default: 30.
.SS "AI Parameters"
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-temperature " " \fINUM\fR
Control response randomness (0.0-2.0). Lower values are more deterministic, higher values more creative. Default: 0.7.
.TP
.BR \-\-max\-tokens " " \fINUM\fR
Maximum tokens in response. Limits response length.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-system " " \fIPROMPT\fR
Custom system prompt to control AI behavior.
.SS "Conversation Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-history " " \fIFILE\fR
Conversation history file for persistent context across sessions.
.TP
.BR \-\-preset " " \fINAME\fR
Use a predefined conversation preset from config file.
.TP
.BR \-\-compare " " \fIMODELS\fR
Compare responses from multiple models (comma-separated list).
.SS "Multimodal Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-image " " \fIFILE\fR
Include image file with request (for vision-capable models).
.TP
.BR \-\-webcam
Capture image from webcam for multimodal input.
.TP
.BR \-\-screenshot
Take screenshot for multimodal input.
.TP
.BR \-\-pdf " " \fIFILE\fR
Process PDF file content.
.TP
.BR \-\-document " " \fIFILE\fR
Process Office document content.
.TP
.BR \-\-batch\-images " " \fIDIR\fR
Process multiple images from directory.
.SS "Voice Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-voice\-input
Enable voice input from microphone.
.TP
.BR \-\-voice\-output
Convert AI response to speech output.
.TP
.BR \-\-voice " " \fINAME\fR
Specify voice to use for text-to-speech.
.SS "Batch Processing"
.TP
.BR \-\-batch " " \fIFILE\fR
Process multiple queries from file, one per line.
.SS "History Management"
.TP
.BR \-\-search\-history " " \fIQUERY\fR
Search through conversation history.
.TP
.BR \-\-export\-history " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Export history to format (json, csv, markdown).
.TP
.BR \-\-history\-stats
Show conversation history statistics.
.TP
.BR \-\-merge\-history " " \fIFILES\fR
Merge multiple history files.
.SS "Workflow Features"
.TP
.BR \-\-workflow " " \fIFILE\fR
Execute workflow from file.
.TP
.BR \-\-list\-workflows
List available workflows.
.SS "Collaboration"
.TP
.BR \-\-share
Share current conversation.
.TP
.BR \-\-collaborate
Start collaboration session.
.SS "Security & Quality"
.TP
.BR \-\-encrypt
Encrypt conversation data.
.TP
.BR \-\-local\-only
Local-only mode (no network access).
.TP
.BR \-\-audit\-log
Enable audit logging.
.TP
.BR \-\-quality\-score
Enable response quality scoring.
.TP
.BR \-\-fact\-check
Enable fact-checking of responses.
.TP
.BR \-\-bias\-detect
Enable bias detection in responses.
.SS "Content Management"
.TP
.BR \-\-template " " \fINAME\fR
Use predefined template.
.TP
.BR \-\-snippet " " \fINAME\fR
Use predefined code snippet.
.TP
.BR \-\-list\-snippets
List available snippets.
.SS "Data Processing"
.TP
.BR \-\-csv " " \fIFILE\fR
Process CSV file.
.TP
.BR \-\-json\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Process JSON file.
.TP
.BR \-\-excel " " \fIFILE\fR
Process Excel file.
.SS "Scheduling"
.TP
.BR \-\-schedule " " \fITIME\fR
Schedule task for later execution.
.SS "Developer Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with detailed logging.
.TP
.BR \-\-test\-mode
Enable test mode with mock responses.
.SS "Configuration"
.TP
.BR \-\-init\-config
Initialize default configuration file at ~/.config/echomind/config.toml.
.TP
.BR \-\-show\-config
Display configuration file location and contents.
.SS "Configuration Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-init\-config
Initialize default configuration file at ~/.config/echomind/config.toml.
.TP
.BR \-\-show\-config
Display configuration file location and contents.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B echomind
can be configured via ~/.config/echomind/config.toml. Use
.B echomind --init-config
to create a default configuration file.

Configuration options include:
.IP \(bu 2
Default API provider and endpoint
.IP \(bu 2
API keys
.IP \(bu 2
Default model selection
.IP \(bu 2
AI parameters (temperature, max_tokens)
.IP \(bu 2
Default modes (coder, stream)
.IP \(bu 2
Request timeout

Command-line options override configuration file settings.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ECHOMIND_API_KEY
API key for authentication. Overrides config file setting but can be overridden by --api-key option.
.SH SUPPORTED PROVIDERS
.TP
.B chat
Free API at https://ch.at (no API key required, GPT-3.5-turbo compatible)
.TP
.B chatanywhere
ChatAnywhere API at https://api.chatanywhere.tech (requires API key, GPT models)
.TP
.B openai
OpenAI API (requires API key, GPT-3.5/4, vision models)
.TP
.B claude
Anthropic Claude API (requires API key, Claude 3 models)
.TP
.B gemini
Google Gemini API (requires API key, Gemini 1.5 Pro, multimodal)
.TP
.B ollama
Local Ollama instance at http://localhost:11434 (no API key, local models)
.TP
.B grok
xAI Grok API (requires API key, Grok models)
.TP
.B mistral
Mistral AI API (requires API key, Mistral models)
.TP
.B cohere
Cohere API (requires API key, Command models)
.TP
.B custom
Custom API endpoint (specify full URL, flexible configuration)
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS "Basic Usage"
.TP
Simple question:
.RS
echo "Hello, how are you?" | echomind
.RE
.TP
Process file contents:
.RS
cat README.md | echomind "Summarize this document"
.RE
.TP
Process command output:
.RS
git diff | echomind "Review these code changes"
.RE
.TP
Read from clipboard:
.RS
echomind --clipboard "Explain this text"
.RE
.SS "Coder Mode"
.TP
Generate code and save to file:
.RS
echo "write a Python factorial function" | echomind --coder --output factorial.py
.RE
.TP
Using shorthand:
.RS
echo "create REST API with FastAPI" | echomind -co api.py
.RE
.SS "Interactive Mode"
.TP
Start interactive conversation:
.RS
echomind --interactive
.RE
.TP
Interactive with streaming and history:
.RS
echomind -i --stream --history session.json
.RE
.SS "Multiple Providers"
.TP
Use OpenAI with GPT-4:
.RS
echo "Explain quantum computing" | echomind --provider openai --model gpt-4
.RE
.TP
Use Claude:
.RS
echo "Write a creative story" | echomind --provider claude --model claude-3-opus
.RE
.TP
Use Gemini:
.RS
echo "Analyze this image" | echomind --provider gemini --model gemini-1.5-pro --image diagram.png
.RE
.TP
Use local Ollama:
.RS
echo "Help me debug this code" | echomind --provider ollama --model llama2
.RE
.SS "Multimodal Features"
.TP
Analyze image:
.RS
echomind --image flowchart.png "Explain this process diagram"
.RE
.TP
Process PDF:
.RS
echomind --pdf document.pdf "Summarize this research paper"
.RE
.TP
Batch process images:
.RS
echomind --batch-images ./photos/ "Describe these images"
.RE
.SS "Voice Features"
.TP
Voice input:
.RS
echomind --voice-input --voice-output "Talk to me"
.RE
.TP
Text to speech:
.RS
echo "Hello world" | echomind --voice-output --voice "alloy"
.RE
.SS "Batch Processing"
.TP
Process multiple queries:
.RS
echo -e "What is AI?\nExplain Rust\nWrite hello world" > queries.txt
echomind --batch queries.txt
.RE
.SS "Model Comparison"
.TP
Compare multiple models:
.RS
echo "Pros and cons of microservices" | echomind --compare "gpt-4,claude-3-opus,gemini-pro"
.RE
.SS "Advanced Parameters"
.TP
Control creativity:
.RS
echo "Write a poem" | echomind --temperature 1.8
.RE
.TP
Precise answers:
.RS
echo "Calculate 15 * 23" | echomind --temperature 0.1
.RE
.TP
Limit response length:
.RS
echo "Explain machine learning" | echomind --max-tokens 100
.RE
.TP
Custom system prompt:
.RS
